#X obj 9 385 comment 646 9 helvetica ? 35584 0 0 0 next send a message
box with a mode name in the right inlet. When sent \, a bang is sent
from the outlet. The pitch class data is stored in a table called "table1"
\, so put a table in your patch called [table table1] and you'll be
able to see the pitch classes from the mode you've just selected. The
pitch class data is also stored in a coll file named scale \, so put
a coll file in your patch called [coll scale]. The coll file includes
a filter which bumps all of the unused pitch classes to a usable (from
the mode) pitch class.;
